DESCRIPTION: Test the continuity of the cable connections between the power supply and control modules, and between each control module, to confirm that electrical connectivity is uninterrupted through the sequence.,
RESULT: All tested cable connections from the power supply through each control module show uninterrupted continuity, with low resistance (0.10 Ω) detected for each path. There are no breaks in electrical connectivity along the measured positive and negative paths. No polarity inversions are present in any of the tested connections.
Current persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:
No circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.


